cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY

This paper discusses a technique for exploiting SQL injection vulnerabilities, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The technique involves using DNS resolution to retrieve malicious SQL query results, which relates to database systems (cs.DB) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also mentions modifications to an open source tool for automating the process, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
